## Build & test

```sh
make build
make test
```

## Run locally

```sh
go run ./cmd/{{.ServiceName}}
```
{{- if .Tenant}}

The `-tenant` scaffold enables strict `X-Tenant-Id` extraction and
Redis-backed tenant cache/idempotency resources. Set `REDIS_URL` or
`REDIS_HOST`/`REDIS_PASSWORD` before starting the service.
{{- end}}
{{- if .Production}}

The `-production` profile is a resource-API baseline. It requires Postgres,
RabbitMQ, a JWKS issuer/audience, and OpenFGA configuration from `.env.example`.
It also requires shared `AUDIT_CHAIN_KEY` and `AUDIT_CURSOR_KEY` values (32+
bytes each) and `make migrate` publishes the audit-log migration alongside the
outbox/inbox migration.
It wires JWT authentication → canonical principal → OpenFGA, then starts a
durable `consume → inbox transaction → outbox relay` command path. Run
`make contracts` in CI with a checked-out baseline as described in the kit CI
recipe.
{{- end}}

## Operate

{{if .Tenant -}}
- Internal readiness endpoint: `GET /ready` on the internal port
- Public routes require `X-Tenant-Id`
{{else -}}
- Health endpoint: `GET /healthz`
{{end -}}
{{if .Production -}}
- Protected endpoint: `GET /v1/status` (JWT + OpenFGA `read` check)
- Durable command queue: `{{.ServiceName}}.commands` → `{{.ServiceName}}.events`
{{end -}}
- Logs: structured JSON to stdout

## Architecture

Wire all dependencies in `internal/app/wire.go`. `kit-doctor .`
audits the wiring against the rho-kit security defaults.

